## Limitations & Caveats

- Regime labels are arbitrary (not ordered bull/bear); interpretation is based on observed statistics.
- HMM assumes Gaussian emissions and first-order Markov transitions — real markets are more complex.
- Clustering methods do not model temporal ordering; only feature-space proximity is used.
- Feature warm-up windows cause the first ~63 trading days to be dropped.
- Results depend on the selected number of regimes ({{ n_regimes }}).

